<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NES emulator as a screensaver?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4394&amp;p=139994#p139994"><![CDATA[
Sorry again for the bump (has it really been 4 years?!?), but I released another new version of the screen saver this morning.  The big news is that this release includes a Mac port along with the standard Windows version!  The Mac version ended up taking a hilarious amount of time longer then I expected which partially explains the long gap between releases.  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />Both versions feature new multi-player support - you can now have separate game &quot;cursors&quot; on the movie wall for each device connected to your PC.  Previously, you only had one game cursor and it was always mapped to your keyboard.  So with this feature you can e.g. have 4 people playing 4 different NES games simultaneously.  Hardly practical but that's never been the point of this software.  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> There's also some other new features and some significant stability improvements.<br /><br />You can check out the official website <a href="http://www.ubernes.com" class="postlink">here</a>, or directly download the <a href="http://www.ubernes.com/data/files/NintendoSaver2015.dmg.gz" class="postlink">Mac version</a> or <a href="http://www.ubernes.com/data/files/NintendoSaver2015.zip" class="postlink">Windows version</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3699">Luke</a> — Tue Jan 27, 2015 5:10 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
